------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-Party Components
------------------------------------------------------------------------

This software has minimal runtime dependencies, by design. The core
canonicalisation logic at v0.1 uses only the Python standard library.

For the complete machine-readable list of dependencies, see the project's
SBOM (Software Bill of Materials) generated for each release in CycloneDX 1.6
format and published alongside the release artefacts on PyPI.

The following third-party components are anticipated for v0.1 (non-exhaustive;
the SBOM published with each release is the authoritative list):

  Runtime:
    (none — Python standard library only)

  Development / testing:
    - pytest (Python) — MIT
    - hypothesis (Python) — Mozilla Public License 2.0
    - ruff (Python) — MIT
    - black (Python) — MIT
    - mypy (Python) — MIT

Each component's full licence text is preserved in the dependency's own
distribution; we do not redistribute their source.

The conformance test corpus imports test vectors from `json-canon` (the Go
reference implementation of RFC 8785, https://github.com/cyberphone/json-canonicalization),
licensed under the Apache License 2.0. Where these vectors are reproduced in
this repository, they remain under their original licence and are credited
in the test-corpus index.

